  "texts": [
    "We evaluate the performance of the auto-encoder in an out-of-distribution (OOD) reconstruction setting by reducing the input grid size to π = 10% of the original spatial grid.",
    "This requires models to reconstruct the full field from very sparse observations-only 12 points on the Advection dataset and 409 points on the Vorticity dataset.",
    "Notably, such extreme sparsity was not encountered during training, where input sampling ratios ranged from π = 20% to π = 100%.",
    "Results This reconstruction experiment demonstrates that ENMA maintains superior reconstruction quality even when provided with extremely sparse input fields.",
    "Among the baselines, AROMA and GINO also exhibit robust performance under such challenging conditions."
  ],
